accessibility.text: Map of the US is FREE!

All the electrical was done by an expert boat electrician and is designed to be able to switch between car battery and the reserve batteries, or switch to the solar charge so you never have to worry about needing a jump.

Nearly black out window covers help keep the light out and people from looking in. The van is fully insulated to keep the you warm during cold nights (like the unexpected snowy weekend we spent in Yellowstone). Some rust on a few spots and wheel wells from all the fun places we have been. We’ve been across the country camping and can vouch for its comfort and fun factor. I made this van be as inconspicuous as possible, from the outside it looks like a normal work van, but once the doors swing open, it’s a lovely living space. It saddens me to have to sell it, but although I can think of plenty of adventures to take it on, I no longer have the time.
